<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
Total body length ranged between 6.5 and 9.1 mm and tail 38.4-40.1% of body length. Hooks 8. Anterior teeth 10 and posterior teeth 12. Rigid and translucent body (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. A Pterosagitta draco (dorsal view) B head C tail D lateral fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; LF = lateral fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704196" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">12</figureCitation>
). Wide and angular head (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. A Pterosagitta draco (dorsal view) B head C tail D lateral fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; LF = lateral fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704196" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">12</figureCitation>
). Wide collarette extending over entire body and reaching anterior of seminal vesicles (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. A Pterosagitta draco (dorsal view) B head C tail D lateral fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; LF = lateral fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704196" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">12A</figureCitation>
. C). Rectangular eyes with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“T”">&quot;T&quot;</normalizedToken>
shaped eye pigments (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. A Pterosagitta draco (dorsal view) B head C tail D lateral fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; LF = lateral fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704196" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">12B</figureCitation>
). Intestinal diverticula absent (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Appearance of body A transparent and flaccid body (Flaccisagitta enflata) B translucent body (Pterosagitta draco) C opaque and rigid body (Aidanosagitta crassa)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704187" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">3B</figureCitation>
). Lateral fins 20.7% of body length. Starting point of lateral fins 65.2% and ending points of lateral fins 86.3% of body length, respectively. One pair of lateral fins triangular-shaped and completely rayed, with forward ends at level of caudal septum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. A Pterosagitta draco (dorsal view) B head C tail D lateral fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; LF = lateral fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704196" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">12A, D</figureCitation>
). Seminal vesicles posteriorly elongated with anterior knob touching lateral fins (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. A Pterosagitta draco (dorsal view) B head C tail D lateral fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; LF = lateral fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704196" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">12C-D</figureCitation>
). Eggs reaching middle of body. Corona ciliata anteriorly opened with horseshoe shape beginning in neck region and ending just behind eyes (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Position and shape of corona ciliata A Aidanosagitta regularis B Pterosagitta draco C Serratosagitta pacifica D Flaccisagitta enflata." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704194" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">10B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. A Pterosagitta draco (dorsal view) B head C tail D lateral fin. Abbreviations: CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; LF = lateral fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704196" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">12A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
